# Kto ya Krol? - eCommerce Styling & Design System

This document outlines the design language, color palette, typography, and interactive elements used to create the premium, editorial feel of the kto ya krol? online store. 

The styling is built entirely with **Tailwind CSS**, utilizing utility classes to maintain a highly responsive and modern interface without writing custom CSS files.

## 🎨 Color Palette

We moved away from standard, default colors to a more sophisticated, high-contrast palette that mimics high-end fashion and lifestyle brands.

* **Background Base:** `bg-[#FAF9F6]`
    * A warm, premium off-white/cream. This prevents eye strain and makes the dark elements pop much more effectively than stark white.
* **Primary Brand Color (Midnight Blue/Dark Slate):** `slate-900` (`#0f172a`)
    * Used for the hero section background, primary typography, buttons, and dark overlays. It is softer than pure black but provides the same high-contrast impact.
* **Text & Accents:** `slate-400`, `slate-500`, `slate-600`
    * Used for paragraphs, secondary descriptions, and subtle borders to create visual hierarchy.
* **Utility & Swatches:** * `green-500` (Toast notification success icon)
    * `amber-700`, `stone-400`, `slate-800` (Mock product color selection swatches)

## 🔤 Typography

The typography relies on extreme contrast in font weights and letter spacing (tracking) to achieve an editorial, magazine-like aesthetic using Tailwind's default `sans` stack.

* **Display Headings (Hero & Section Titles):**
    * Classes: `font-black`, `uppercase`, `tracking-tighter` (e.g., `text-6xl md:text-8xl`)
    * Style: Massive, heavy, uppercase text with squished letter spacing for high impact.
* **Navigation & Micro-Labels (Buttons, Links):**
    * Classes: `font-bold`, `uppercase`, `tracking-widest`, `text-xs`
    * Style: Very small, highly spaced, bold text. This acts as a structural anchor and looks incredibly sleek.
* **Body Copy (Descriptions):**
    * Classes: Normal weight, `text-slate-500` or `text-slate-600`, `leading-relaxed`
    * Style: Clean, breathable text for easy reading.

## ⬜ Shapes & UI Components

* **Buttons:** Fully rounded "pill" shapes (`rounded-full`). They typically feature inverted hover states (e.g., solid dark background swapping to a dark outline on hover) to encourage interaction.
* **Hero Section:** Features a unique bottom-border radius (`rounded-b-[3rem]`) to break up the standard boxy website grid and create a sweeping, soft transition into the product section.
* **Product Cards:** Subtle rounding (`rounded-2xl`) with very light borders (`border-gray-100`) and soft shadows (`shadow-sm`) that dramatically increase on hover (`hover:shadow-xl`).
* **Image Framing:** Products are locked into specific aspect ratios (e.g., `aspect-square`, `aspect-[4/5]`) with light gray backdrops (`bg-gray-50`) to ensure all product photography looks uniform, even if the source images vary in size.

## ✨ Animations & Interactions

Micro-interactions are critical for making the site feel expensive and responsive.

* **Product Hover States:**
    * Images slowly zoom in (`scale-110`, `duration-700`) to draw the eye.
    * The "Add to Cart" button slides up from the bottom (`translate-y-4` to `translate-y-0`) paired with a dark fade (`opacity-0` to `opacity-100`).
* **Quick View Modal:**
    * Uses a `backdrop-blur-sm` to keep the user grounded on the current page.
    * Features a combined fade, scale, and slide animation (`translate-y-12 scale-95 opacity-0` to `translate-y-0 scale-100 opacity-100`) triggered by a microscopic `10ms` delay to ensure buttery smooth browser rendering without lag.
* **Toast Notifications:**
    * Slides up from the bottom right corner when an item is added to the cart, automatically dismissing after 3 seconds.